.el .ds Aq '
.TH import-curl 1  "import-curl " 
.SH NAME
import\-curl \- Take a curl invocation (e.g. from Burp\*(Aqs "Copy as cURL"), run scan against the parsed target
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBimport\-curl\fR [\fB\-\-curl\-file\fR] [\fB\-\-from\-stdin\fR] <\fB\-\-param\fR> <\fB\-\-payload\fR> [\fB\-\-level\fR] [\fB\-\-delay\-ms\fR] [\fB\-\-insecure\fR] [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-\-only\fR] [\fB\-\-exclude\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Take a curl invocation (e.g. from Burp\*(Aqs "Copy as cURL"), run scan against the parsed target
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-curl\-file\fR \fI<CURL_FILE>\fR
Path to a file containing a curl invocation. Mutually exclusive with `\-\-from\-stdin`
.TP
\fB\-\-from\-stdin\fR
Read the curl invocation from stdin. Mutually exclusive with `\-\-curl\-file`
.TP
\fB\-\-param\fR \fI<PARAM>\fR
Query/body parameter name to inject the payload into. Must already exist in the parsed curl request OR will be appended
.TP
\fB\-\-payload\fR \fI<PAYLOAD>\fR
Raw payload to mutate via the evasion engine
.TP
\fB\-\-level\fR \fI<LEVEL>\fR [default: heavy]
Evasion intensity. Maps to `wafrift scan \-\-level`
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
light
.IP \(bu 2
medium
.IP \(bu 2
heavy
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-delay\-ms\fR \fI<DELAY_MS>\fR [default: 50]
Inter\-request delay in milliseconds
.TP
\fB\-\-insecure\fR
Disable TLS verification (lab targets only)
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR [default: text]
Output format: `text` (default) or `json`
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
text
.IP \(bu 2
json
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-only\fR \fI<ONLY>...\fR
Restrict to listed technique paths (comma\-separated)
.TP
\fB\-\-exclude\fR \fI<EXCLUDE>...\fR
Drop listed technique paths (comma\-separated)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
